			<description><![CDATA[<p><strong><strong>R7 Solutions is adding a new member to our software development team. We are seeking an early-career to mid-career developer.</strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>We focus on building small, highly effective technical teams that can deliver innovative geospatial intelligence, workflow and integration solutions to clients in a wide range of industries. </strong></p>
<p><strong>We need candidates who are smart, disciplined and able to work independently  when required, but also know how to contribute to a team. </strong></p>
<p>We  are an entrepreneurial company developing custom .NET software, Web 2.0  interfaces and geospatial business solutions for the oil and gas,  alternative energy, pipeline and right-of-way industries.</p>
<p>Our website is  at <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.r7solutions.com/">http://www.R7Solutions.com</a>.</p>
<p><strong><strong>Requirements:</strong></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Strong professional software development interest</li>
<li>Organized, disciplined approach to problem-solving</li>
<li>Computer science degree or equivalent experience</li>
<li>Good experience with ASP.NET 2.0 or later and SQL Server</li>
<li>Silverlight, GIS, or other specialized skills are a plus</li>
<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li>
<li>Good professional presentation and client-interaction skills</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Development of innovative Web 2.0+ online services</li>
<li>Feature and interface design to deliver remarkable functionality and ease to the user; UX rules.</li>
<li>Participation on a product design team responsible for pioneering the future of geospatial business applications</li>
<li>Ongoing development and support for client software, including web-based enterprise business process management, workflow and intelligence systems</li>
<li>Keeping up with new tools and techniques, including the latest software from Microsoft and third-party tools</li>
</ul>
<p>You should be professional but inform  al and unafraid of taking the lead  in proposing and developing client solutions or new software features.</p>
<p>You will be working on custom client software and on internal product  development for our hosted services and enterprise software.</p>
<p><strong>Leadership,  design and innovation opportunities are constantly available.</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>We are a certified Microsoft and ESRI business partner. We also keep up  with the latest technologies (ASP.NET 4.0, Silverlight 4.0, ArcGIS 10,  Azure and other cloud services, etc.).</p>
<p>This is a full-time position, including access to  group health insurance for individuals and dependents, prescription  coverage, professional development opportunities and camaraderie with  like-minded technologists and business people.</p>
<p><strong>When applying focus on  your cover letter, not your resume! </strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>Local applications only, please. International sponsorships not  available. Principals only - No third-party applications. Equal  Opportunity Employer. <!-- START CLTAGS --></p>]]></description>
